cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use this software in your research, please cite it using the metadata below."
type: software
title: "emotional-memory: Affective Field Theory for LLM Memory"
abstract: >
  A Python library implementing Affective Field Theory (AFT) — a 5-layer
  emotional model for LLM memory that integrates valence-arousal affect
  (Russell 1980), affective momentum (Spinoza), mood fields (Heidegger),
  appraisal vectors (Scherer CPM), and resonance links with spreading
  activation (Collins & Loftus 1975) and Hebbian strengthening (Hebb 1949).
